La Lomita is a well liked and friendly neighborhood restaurant but it is benefiting mightily from being one of a few Hill East restaurants.  The food is average and is overpriced.  The restaurant is in bad shape.  The  patio is rotten, the landscaping is an eye sore and the inside of the restaurant is sorely in need of updating.  Worst part is the trash just behind the patio attracts rats.  I have seen them around the restaurant and dead in the street in front of the restaurant.  I have never seen a rat inside the restaurant but I have seen them just outside of the doors near their trash. There are several new restaurants coming to Hill East at the Blackbird building and Beckett’s Park on E st.  La Lomita will go out of business or be forced to renovate with their business going to nicer establishments.  I am pulling for the restaurant but they must reinvest capital into the business to keep attracting people once Hill East has more options.  Those options will be on line by Summer 2020.
